{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b35e2e21-699c-4b7e-9438-fe1ac69a20b0","content":"The issue is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference modules defined in files listed *before* them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but is listed first.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_rLGdGjtLbAIRtkebUDhnWS","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-4c5fa631e03e45ed9fff0ba1df4ffbd3/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-4c5fa631e03e45ed9fff0ba1df4ffbd3/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"f96501b2-0e3e-41b6-9440-bd304e89ebd5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed before them in the project file. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n```xml\n<Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n<Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n<Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n```\n\n`Services.fs` is listed first but it depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`). `Domain.fs` needs to come before `Services.fs`.\n\nThe correct order should be:\n1. `Domain.fs` (defines the types)\n\n\n2. `Services.fs` (uses Domain types)\n3. `Program.fs` (uses both)","outputTokens":458,"requestId":"F028:BCCDE:257B2F4:2982DD6:69F93E96"},"id":"0289639f-b019-4152-b7a4-9cfcabf5389b","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:49:35.186Z","parentId":"02d2e045-47ae-496d-af27-5b24827dd59a"}
